# Collapse

`TxCollapse` groups expandable panels and controls their active names through `v-model`. `TxCollapseItem` renders a semantic button header and an animated content region.

Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/collapse/src/types.ts`, `TxCollapse.vue`, `TxCollapseItem.vue`, and `collapse.test.ts`.

## Basic Usage

::::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="CollapseBasicDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const active = ref(['first'])
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxCollapse v-model="active">
      <TxCollapseItem title="Getting Started" name="first">
        Starter content goes here.
      </TxCollapseItem>
      <TxCollapseItem title="Advanced" name="second">
        Extra options and settings.
      </TxCollapseItem>
    </TxCollapse>
